  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.1379" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>39, Hornby [Road], Bombay,<lb/> 5.<hi rendition="#sup">th</hi> May 1882.</dateline>
        <opener>My dear Sir,</opener>
        <p>I have had the pleasure of receiving your letter of the 7.<hi
            rendition="#sup">th</hi> January, to which I now beg to reply, asking you to excuse me for the delay, caused by the nature of the inquiries I had to institute concerning the works published in <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.4423">Indo-Portuguese dialects</ref>.</p>
        <p>The <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.844">Portuguese</ref> spoken in the Portuguese colonies of <placeName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.348">Goa</placeName>, <placeName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.5902">Damão</placeName> and <placeName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.553">Diu</placeName> is as pure as that of <placeName>
Lisbon</placeName>. <pb
            facs="#IMG.2"
            n="2"/>The dialects are spoken in the so called Portuguese Province of the North, now under the British rule, consisting of Thaná,<note
            n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <foreign
                xml:lang="de">Gemeint ist <placeName>

Thane</placeName>. Thane ist eine Stadt im Groβraum der Metropole <placeName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.178">
Mumbai</placeName>
            </foreign>.</note>
          <placeName>
Bassein</placeName>
          <note n="2" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <foreign xml:lang="de">Gemeint ist Vasai. Vasai ist ein Teil der Vasai-Virar Stadt und liegt nördlich von Mumbai.</foreign>

          </note> and the neighbourhood, the ancient Province of the South, also under the British, comprising <placeName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.5858">Mangalore</placeName>, <placeName>
Cochim</placeName> [etc.], and <placeName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.5857">Ceylon</placeName>; <placeName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.5908">Syngapure</placeName> + <placeName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.5979">Malacca</placeName>. With the exception of the dialect of Ceylon, there is no work published in any other dialect. All these dialects are closely related, and that of Ceylon may be taken as the type of them. With regard to this latter dialect you have already all the work hitherto published, such as the New Testament, and are [aware] of the grammatical <pb
            facs="#IMG.3" n="3"/>work on the subject. But you do not seem to possess the <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">Livro de oraçãos</hi>,<note n="3" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <foreign xml:lang="de">Gemeint ist vermutlich das folgende Werk:</foreign>
            <bibl>

1841. <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">O livro de oraçãos usados ne grejas de Wesleyanos ne iye de Ceylon</hi>. Colombo: empressado ne officio Wesleyano.
</bibl>
          </note> published at <placeName>

Colombo</placeName> in the Ceylon Indo-Portuguese dialect. A copy of this work I beg to present you now.</p>
        <p>I shall be most happy to assist you in your interesting and valuable investigations, and shall be too glad to answer any other question you may in future deem it necessary to address to me.</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Believe me, my dear Sir,</salute>
          <lb/>
          <salute>Yours very truly</salute>
          <lb/>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1355">
              <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">J. Gerson da Cunha</hi>
            </persName>
          </signed>. </closer>
        <pb facs="#IMG.4" n="4"/>
      </div>
